replies.bodyText:
The max length is for the parameter type list, while the mediumtext is for parameters, which has a greater length than the parameter type list.
For example, for a parameter type list int,varchar, the parameter may be:
[ {
  "name" : "p1",
  "type" : "int"
}, {
  "name" : "p2",
  "type" : "varchar"
} ]

The 1) length of the parameter names, 2) the number of parameters, 3) the JSON-encoding characters may expand the total size.
I think we should also place limits on the parameter name length and the parameter counts. That can help us maintain the total length of parameters within text, although only by a small margin.

